
  <sn><md>#### Mesopotamian Civilization

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
The **Mesopotamian Civilization** is one of the oldest civilizations in the world. Around `5000 BCE`, it developed in `Iraq` (also known as Mesopotamia), along the fertile banks of the `Tigris` (Dijla) and `Euphrates` (Furat) rivers.

Although these rivers had different names, the ++civilizations that developed in this same geographical region are collectively called the Mesopotamian Civilization++. The term **“Mesopotamia”** is of Greek origin, meaning `land between two rivers`

In the present world, the territories of `Iraq, Syria, Iran, and Kuwait` were part of this ancient civilization, though ++most of it++ is located in modern-day `Iraq`.

  :::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://kajabi-storefronts-production.kajabi-cdn.com/kajabi-storefronts-production/file-uploads/themes/2153245919/settings_images/4afdcf3-657a-8abe-2478-dddc3163b57_VgFiMV19QVaBqniL0WXE_pasted_image_0_19.png)
:::
:::


The Mesopotamian Civilization includes several major civilizations:

* Sumerian Civilization
* Babylonian Civilization
* Assyrian Civilization
* Chaldean Civilization</md></sn>
